description: Midsummer AB engages in the manufacture and supply of solar energy technology solutions for the production and installation of thin film solar panels. The company is headquartered in Jarfalla, Stockholm and currently employs 109 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2018-06-21. The Company’s technology enables to manufacture customized lightweight flexible solar panels, which can be attached onto any type of surface. Applications comprise floating modules, vehicles, landfills, portable power generation and membrane roofs on factories, offices and other structures that are not strong enough for traditional glass modules. Products consist of the DUO, mass production deposition equipment, as well as the UNO, a research and development (R&D) tool, which is made in different configurations. Process improvements in R&D are directly transferable to the DUO production tools.
naics: Semiconductor and Other Electronic Component Manufacturing
